## Overcoming Challenges in Agile Product Management

### Balancing Flexibility with Structure

While flexibility is a hallmark of Agile, too much can lead to chaos. Establishing some degree of structure ensures that the team remains focused and productive.

### Managing Stakeholder Expectations

Frequent changes can sometimes lead to stakeholder frustration. It's crucial to communicate the value of Agile and manage expectations through regular updates and demos.

### Ensuring Consistent Team Alignment

With frequent iterations and changes, maintaining team alignment can be challenging. Regular communication and clear documentation of decisions are essential.

